### Refresh Token Rotation Strategy

Store refresh tokens in an encrypted database with metadata (issued date, family ID for detecting reuse). On each token refresh, issue a new refresh token and invalidate the old one. If an old token is reused, invalidate the entire token family to detect compromised tokens. Use short expiration windows (7 days) and rotate tokens on every refresh request.

```typescript
interface RefreshTokenRecord {
  tokenHash: string;
  familyId: string;
  issuedAt: Date;
  expiresAt: Date;
  revoked: boolean;
}

const rotateRefreshToken = async (oldToken: string) => {
  const record = await db.findRefreshToken(oldToken);
  if (record.revoked) throw new Error('Token family compromised');

  await db.revokeTokenFamily(record.familyId);
  return generateNewRefreshToken(record.familyId);
};
```

**Common interview trap:** Forgetting to invalidate the entire token family when reuse is detected, allowing an attacker to continue using compromised tokens.

